    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Type of insanity, described by ancient writers, in which the patient imagines himself to be a wolf, with the instincts and propensities of a wolf. Also, more generally applied to those forms of insanity in which the patient imagines himself a beast. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
